{{Quote|It could have bombed! It was a comicbook concept, dressed up for the screen. ''[''&hellip;'']'' Therefore, what could be more proper, more apt, more totally fitting than to present the magic of ''STAR WARS'' in comicbook form&mdash;and thus do we come full circle!|Excerpt of Stan Lee's introduction|<ref name="Marvel" />}}
'''''The Marvel Comics Illustrated Version of Star Wars''''' is a [[Star Wars Legends|Legends]] [[Star Wars comic books|trade paperback]] that collects the first six issues of the [[Marvel Comics|Marvel]] comic-book series [[Star Wars (1977)|''Star Wars'']], reprinted in a smaller size in black and white. The book was adapted by [[Roy Thomas]] and [[Howard Chaykin]] from [[George Lucas]]'s screenplay for the film [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|''Star Wars'': Episode IV ''A New Hope'']].

It also includes a special introduction written by [[Stan Lee]], as well as a gallery of pin-ups illustrated by Chaykin and [[Ernie Chan]]. ''The Marvel Comics Illustrated Version of Star Wars'' was published by [[Del Rey]] in [[November]] [[1977]].

==Publisher's summary==
''Across the teeming reaches of a galaxy in the grip of evil&hellip;''

''Hurtling headlong through hyper-space ''[''sic'']'' to subdue the dark champions of tyranny&hellip;''

''Blazing through the cosmos on a mission of vengeance and honor, comes''

''Luke Skywalker''

''proud young Rebel pledged to restore justice to the universe and rescue the beautiful Princess Leia from the deadly Imperial forces!''

''Join him and the dauntless Han Solo, Obi-Wan Kenobi, Artoo Detoo, See Threepio and Chewbacca in the greatest space fantasy adventure ever!''

